            "title": "Ganfeng Lithium Returns to Annual Net Profit",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Jason Chau </p><br/><p>\n  China's Ganfeng Lithium returned to profitability in 2025, supported by a recovery in sales volumes and prices. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  The lithium producer said Tuesday it swung to a net profit of 1.61 billion yuan last year, equivalent to $232.9 million, from a 2.07 billion yuan net loss in 2024. </p><p>\n\n  Revenue rose to 22.80 billion yuan in 2025 from 18.73 billion yuan in the previous year. </p><p>\n\n  The Chinese lithium producer attributed the return to profitability to a recovery in sales prices and a jump in sales volumes for its lithium salts and battery products, driven by shifts in supply and demand. </p><p>\n\n  Stronger operating revenue, increased gains from disposals of subsidiaries, stakes in associate companies and its financial assets also supported 2025 results, the company said. </p><p>\n\n  Ganfeng's Hong Kong-listed shares were last trading 1.4% lower, while its Shenzhen-listed shares were last down 0.7%. </p><p>\n\n  Looking ahead, Citi expects mixed first-quarter results, with weaker margins at its battery segment partly offset by higher lithium prices and cost-saving measures. </p><p>\n\n  Ganfeng, China's largest lithium compounds producer and the world's biggest lithium metal supplier, is a key player in the country's new energy supply chain. It products are used in industries including electric vehicles and energy storage. </p><br/><p>\n  Write to Jason Chau at jason.chau@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  03-30-26 2255ET</p></div>",
